> [PWA] Refactoring state machine into AppBannerManager.

>

> This CL is the next incremental step into removing all of the

> inheritance in the AppBannerManager system. It does this by:

entry.title: Remove `forced_colors` and `is_dark_mode` from UpdateSystemColorInfo()
entry.content:
This CL cleans up of the UpdateSystemColorInfo() pipeline by removing

the `forced_colors` and `is_dark_mode` param. Originally, this pipeline

was designed to inform Blink of the system color info states changes.

However, with system colors now being retrieved from color providers

(CL:5322440) and forced colors now existing as a Web setting

(CL:5368321), these params have become redundant and therefore can be

safely removed.

entry.title: CopyEI2T: Handle Copying from Rotated VideoFrame
entry.content:
In current implementation, HTMLVE/VideoFrame as CopyEI2T source

uses natural_size()/coded_size() as source size to do validation

and copy rect calculation.



However, this is not correct when video source contains rotation

metadata. Rotated 90 or 270 degree switches video frame width and

height. WebCodec VideoFrame defines "displayWidth/Height" for this.



This CL updated video source size from natural size to display

size to handle rotated video frames.

entry.title: [infra] Update the format of keys used when not specifying an ID.
entry.content:
Currently for an unscoped node type with allow_empty_id=True, if a key

ID isn't specified the nodes library creates a key where the ID value

for the _CHROMIUM_NS is set to "UNIQUE", which prevents collisions if

the generated sequence value is the same as an explicitly provided ID

value. However, this means that there could be collisions if the node

type's kind is used as the scoped node type:



Example using bundles and per-test modifications:



key for anonymous bundle with ID generated as "1"

[("@chromium", "UNIQUE"), ("targets|bundle", "1")]

key for bundle with name "1"

[("@chromium", ""), ("targets|bundle", "1")]



key for modification to test foo in anonymous bundle

[("@chromium", ""), ("targets|bundle", "1"), ("targets|test", "foo")]

key for modification to test foo in bundle 1

[("@chromium", ""), ("targets|bundle", "1"), ("targets|test", "foo")]



While it us unlikely that someone would define an entity with an

entirely numeric name, it's not impossible and the use of an entirely

numeric ID for unname entities can produce confusing error messages.



To address the possibility of conflicts and improve error messages for

nodes using a generated ID, this changes the code to instead append the

number to a prefix that clearly identifies an unnamed declaration. When

explicitly specifying a key ID, it cannot begin with the prefix used for

anonymous IDs.

entry.title: media/gpu/V4L2StatefulVD: Don't signal |flush_cb_| if there's pending work
entry.content:
This CL fixes a corner case where ToT signals |flush_cb_| (indicating

the flush caused by end_of_stream() is finished done) when there's

still work to be done in the |OUTPUT_queue_|.



This issue was found out by vp80-03-segmentation-1436.ivf, which is

composed of two different resolution I-frames. The second frame

causes a resolution change which itself causes a |CAPTURE_queue_|

reconfiguration. Since the second configuration is detected in a

background thread (in a blocking poll in WaitOnceForEvents()), it

races with running said |flush_cb_|.



Re-reading the spec [1] there's some wording about this:

"Any OUTPUT buffers queued by the client before the VIDIOC_DECODER_CMD()

was issued will be processed and decoded as normal. The client must

continue to handle both queues independently, similarly to normal

decode operation. This includes:



- handling any operations triggered as a result of processing those

buffers, such as the Dynamic Resolution Change sequence, before

continuing with the drain sequence,

- queuing and dequeuing CAPTURE buffers, until a buffer marked with

the V4L2_BUF_FLAG_LAST flag is dequeued,

"



I understood that the LAST buffer was held until all work was processed

and finalized but from the test vector above, I see the spec can be

read as: wait until |OUTPUT_queue_| is truly empty, then look for the

LAST buffer coming out of the |CAPTURE_queue_|. This is what this CL

does, and it seem to fix the race and still verifies all test vectors

on Hana and Trogdor (minus some vp8_comprehensive ones on hana which

is tracked in b/b/303864839)



[1] https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/v5.15/userspace-api/media/v4l/dev-decoder.html#drain



Bug: 329051390

Change-Id: I7c9a5c1b8a312fb46eefefa0fbdee89a9172258f

Reviewed-on: https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/5398057
